These are Puzzles for 2x2 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-1::.
There 2 different types of food: artichoke, apricot
The people use 2 different means of transport: taxi, van
1. the person driving the taxi is on the right of the person driving the van##1
2. the person eating artichoke is not to the right of the person driving the van##8

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |    2     |
| Food        | artichoke   | apricot   |
| Transport   | van | taxi |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-2::.
There are 2 different favourite beverages: lemonade, mirinda
The people prefer 2 different types of sport: baseball, parkour
1. the person who's sport is baseball is not to the left of the person drinking mirinda##8
2. the person who's sport is baseball is somewhere to the right of the person drinking mirinda##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |    2    |
| Beverage   | mirinda | lemonade   |
| Sport      | parkour | baseball |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-3::.
There 2 different types of food: asparagus, cauliflower
The people prefer 2 different music-genres: blues, folk
1. the person eating asparagus is not to the left of the fan of folk##8
2. the person eating cauliflower is on the left of the fan of folk##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |    2    |
| Food          | cauliflower | asparagus |
| Music-Genre   | blues   | folk     |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-4::.
